    narr:generatedFrom "dfe24ea36989033f650ec43c133a10dd7d5ee180" ;
    narr:narration """This hub collects style-metrics records across the full document corpus — register profiles, voice ratios, jargon density readings, and sentence-length patterns extracted from memos, call transcripts, design sessions, engineering logs, and voice memos. The dominant signature named repeatedly across children is the Scarlet session-memo idiolect: antithesis-heavy structure, active voice dominant in editorial prose, short punchy declaratives at conviction peaks, and blockquoted speech that is run-on and filler-heavy. This pattern is attested from early March 2026 through mid-July, appearing in [strategic decision memos](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleMetrics_CalibratedGrowth_20260527), [correction memos](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Metrics_Correction_Tranche2_20260612), [retrospective reflections](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Metrics_SessionReflection_20260416), [sales call notes](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Metrics_TemporalityValidation_20260501), and [pitch-reframe memos](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleMetrics_PitchReframeReview_20260521). Engineering and technical documents form a distinct register cluster: [post-mortem evaluations](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleMetrics_EnterpriseCustomerWeekOne) carry high system-specific jargon density with authoritative action-oriented tone, while [infrastructure decision logs](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleMetrics_LensArchRevision) are engineering-internal with imperative and declarative constructions. A third cluster covers voice-memo and transcript registers — [morning-pages style](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleMetrics_Moonshot_20260701) with raw stream-of-consciousness blockquotes averaging ~35 words per sentence, contrasting sharply with tighter editorial framing prose. The [voice-rule memo](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Metrics_ScarletVoiceRule_20260612) and [founding story](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Metrics_FoundingStory) mark stylistic poles: one a short decision-memo with very low jargon density, the other high lexical diversity with technical embedding-space vocabulary. Outlier registers include [the discovery consultant call](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleMetrics_DiscoveryConsultantCall) with high RDF/SPARQL/ABAC jargon density and passive voice in analytical framing, and [the EVFlocking application](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleMetrics_EVFlockingApplication) where a lyrical founder essay is wrapped in a technical session-memo shell.""" ;
